  description: The tmux capture-pane command uses {session_name} without quoting: f"tmux capture-pane -t {session_name}". While the current patch correctly focuses on working_dir, this represents a similar command injection vector if session_name could contain shell metacharacters (e.g., derived from untrusted task IDs). However, session_name is likely internally generated and safe; this is noted for completeness but outside the scope of the working_dir security fix.

